
The files with the extension .ul are sound files.
They are encoded in 16kHz, mu-law, mono.

If you have the program sox installed, you can play them like this:
 $ play -r 16k introsnd.ul

You can use sox to convert soundfiles from other formats:
 $ sox mysound.wav -c 1 introsnd.ul rate 16k


The soundfiles 
errorsnd.ul, infosnd.ul, introsnd.ul, rightsnd.ul, wrongsnd.ul,
neutralsnd.ul
of the original AKFQuiz package are put into the Public Domain.
